Class SortableTreeNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.tree.DefaultMutableTreeNode
      • aims.photo.uploader.tablemodels.SortableTreeNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.tree.MutableTreeNode, javax.swing.tree.TreeNode

    public class SortableTreeNode
extends javax.swing.tree.DefaultMutableTreeNode
    Created with IntelliJ IDEA. User: Timothy Hart Date: 12/13/12 Time: 12:56 PM

    SortableTreeNode is a specific DefaultMutableTreeNode node object that contains the full functionality of a DefaultMutableTreeNode and incoporates an auto-sorting method for use when merging new Tree Nodes into existing Nodes.

    SortableTreeNode achieves this by using a Comparator inside the overridden insert method.

    Author:
    Timothy Hart
